# S01-T07: Priority-based Shared Rendering Scheduler

## Objective
Port and enhance the AnimationManager from drone-interface/6 into a priority-based rendering scheduler for React. NOT one rAF per component — a central frame scheduler with priority rendering and adaptive pipeline.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `src/services/RenderScheduler.ts` — Singleton class with:
  - Single rAF loop shared across all consumers
  - **Priority levels**: CRITICAL (attitude gauges, compass), NORMAL (radar, graphs), LOW (decorative effects)
  - CRITICAL callbacks run every frame
  - NORMAL callbacks run at 30 FPS (every other frame at 60hz)
  - LOW callbacks run at 15 FPS (every 4th frame at 60hz)
  - Adaptive: when FPS drops below threshold, LOW callbacks are suspended, then NORMAL reduced
  - Frame budget monitoring: warns if callbacks exceed 16ms total
  - register(callback, priority) / unregister(id) API
  - Drift compensation
  - Auto-start/stop lifecycle
- `src/shared/hooks/useRenderCallback.ts` — React hook wrapping register/unregister:
  - `useRenderCallback(drawFn, priority)` — auto-cleanup on unmount
  - Returns `{ isActive, fps }` state
- `src/shared/hooks/useAnimationFrame.ts` — Simpler hook for one-off animations (non-Canvas)

## Reference
- Source: `drone-interface/6/src/composables/useAnimationManager.ts` (128 lines, singleton pattern)
- Enhancement: priority scheduling is NEW — not in drone-interface/6

## Steps
1. Port AnimationManager class from drone-interface/6
2. Add priority enum: CRITICAL, NORMAL, LOW
3. Implement per-priority frame skipping logic
4. Add frame budget monitoring
5. Create useRenderCallback hook with auto-cleanup
6. Create useAnimationFrame hook for simple cases
